OVERVIEW: Set build configurations for scheme actions

USAGE: xcodeproj-cli set-scheme-config [--project <project>] [--workspace <workspace>] [--verbose] [--dry-run] <scheme-name> [--build <build>] [--run <run>] [--test <test>] [--profile <profile>] [--analyze <analyze>] [--archive <archive>]

ARGUMENTS:
  <scheme-name>           Name of the scheme to configure

OPTIONS:
  -p, --project <project> Path to .xcodeproj file (default: looks for
                          *.xcodeproj in current directory)
  -w, --workspace <workspace>
                          Path to .xcworkspace file
  -V, --verbose           Enable verbose output with performance metrics
  --dry-run               Preview changes without saving
  --build <build>         Set build configuration
  --run <run>             Set run configuration
  --test <test>           Set test configuration
  --profile <profile>     Set profile configuration
  --analyze <analyze>     Set analyze configuration
  --archive <archive>     Set archive configuration
  --version               Show the version.
  -h, --help              Show help information.

